hist only depends on coordinates 0..n of ω.1 and on ω.2. Concretely,
changing ω.1 at indices > n does not affect hist alg ω n.

PROVIDED SOLUTION
By induction on n.
Base case (n=0): hist uses ω.1 0. extendIic 0 (fun i ↦ ω.1 i) 0 = ω.1 0 (by definition, since 0 ≤ 0). So the two hist values are equal.

Inductive step (n → n+1): wait, we need hist at n, not n+1. Let me re-read the statement...

Actually the statement is: hist alg ω n = hist alg (extendIic n (fun i : Iic n ↦ ω.1 i), ω.2) n

For n=0: both sides compute using ω.1 0 (resp. extendIic 0 ... 0 = ω.1 0) and ω.2, so they're equal.

For n+1: hist alg ω (n+1) uses hist alg ω n, ω.1 (n+1), and ω.2.
hist alg (ext, ω.2) (n+1) uses hist alg (ext, ω.2) n, ext (n+1), and ω.2.
By IH, hist alg (extendIic (n+1) ..., ω.2) n = ?

Wait, the IH at n gives: hist alg ω n = hist alg (extendIic n (fun i : Iic n ↦ ω.1 i), ω.2) n
But we need: hist alg (extendIic (n+1) (fun i : Iic (n+1) ↦ ω.1 i), ω.2) n

The issue is that extendIic (n+1) and extendIic n produce different functions, but they agree on {0,...,n}. So we'd need a lemma that hist only looks at ω.1 at indices ≤ n.

This might need a stronger induction hypothesis. Actually, the cleanest approach might be:
Show by induction that for any two ω, ω' : probSpace α R with ω.1 i = ω'.1 i for all i ≤ n and ω.2 = ω'.2, we have hist alg ω n = hist alg ω' n.
-/
lemma hist_eq_hist_extendIic (alg : Algorithm α R) (n : ℕ) (ω : probSpace α R) :
    hist alg ω n = hist alg (extendIic n (fun i : Iic n ↦ ω.1 i), ω.2) n := by
  refine' Nat.recOn n _ _ <;> simp_all +decide [ hist_add_one_eq_IicSuccProd ];
  · unfold extendIic; aesop;
  · intro n hn
    have h_eq : ∀ i : Iic n, ω.1 i = (extendIic (n + 1) (fun i : Iic (n + 1) => ω.1 i)) i := by
      intro i
      simp [extendIic];
      grind
    generalize_proofs at *;
    have h_eq : ∀ (ω ω' : probSpace α R), (∀ i : Iic n, ω.1 i = ω'.1 i) ∧ ω.2 = ω'.2 → hist alg ω n = hist alg ω' n := by
      refine' Nat.recOn n _ _ <;> simp_all +decide [ hist_add_one_eq_IicSuccProd' ];
      intro n hn ω ω' h_eq h_eq' ; specialize hn ω ω' ( fun a ha ↦ h_eq a ( Nat.le_succ_of_le ha ) ) h_eq' ; aesop;
    generalize_proofs at *;
    refine' ⟨ h_eq _ _ ⟨ _, rfl ⟩, _, _ ⟩ <;> simp_all +decide [ action_add_one_eq, reward_add_one ];
    · intro i hi; simp +decide [ extendIic, hi ] ;
      grind;
    · unfold extendIic; simp +decide ;
      grind;
    · unfold extendIic; simp +decide [ Finset.mem_Iic ] ;
      grind

/-
PROBLEM
hist alg ω n factors through (fun i : Iic n ↦ ω.1 i, ω.2) via a measurable function.

PROVIDED SOLUTION
Take f = fun p => hist alg (extendIic n p.1, p.2) n.
Measurability: f = (hist alg · n) ∘ (fun p => (extendIic n p.1, p.2)). Both are measurable.
Equality: by hist_eq_hist_extendIic.
-/
lemma hist_factors_through_pair (alg : Algorithm α R) (n : ℕ) :
    ∃ f : ((Iic n → I) × (ℕ → α → R)) → (Iic n → α × R),
      Measurable f ∧ ∀ ω : probSpace α R, hist alg ω n = f (fun i ↦ ω.1 i, ω.2) := by
  have h_measurable : Measurable (fun ω : (Iic n → I) × (ℕ → α → R) => hist alg (extendIic n ω.1, ω.2) n) := by
    have h_measurable : Measurable (fun ω : probSpace α R => hist alg ω n) := by
      exact?
    generalize_proofs at *;
    exact h_measurable.comp ( Measurable.prodMk ( measurable_extendIic n |> Measurable.comp <| measurable_fst ) measurable_snd );
  exact ⟨ _, h_measurable, fun ω => by rw [ hist_eq_hist_extendIic ] ⟩

/-
PROBLEM
Under infinitePi, coordinate n+1 is independent from coordinates in Iic n.

PROVIDED SOLUTION
Use iIndepFun_infinitePi to get mutual independence of coordinates under infinitePi.
Then use IndepFun_iff_Indep to reformulate.
Note that comap (fun f => fun i : Iic n => f i) = ⨆ i : Iic n, comap (eval i) (by comap_pi).
Apply indep_iSup_of_disjoint with S = {n+1} and T = Iic n (as a subset of ℕ).
These are disjoint since n+1 ∉ Iic n.
The iIndep comes from iIndepFun_infinitePi converted to iIndep.
-/
lemma indepFun_eval_restrict_infinitePi (n : ℕ) :
    IndepFun (fun (f : ℕ → I) ↦ f (n + 1))
      (fun f ↦ fun (i : Iic n) ↦ f i)
      (Measure.infinitePi fun _ ↦ (volume : Measure I)) := by
  -- The coordinate n+1 is independent from the coordinates in Iic n under the infinitePi measure.
  have h_indep : IndepFun (fun f : ℕ → I => f (n + 1)) (fun f : ℕ → I => fun i : Iic n => f i) (Measure.infinitePi fun _ => ℙ) := by
    have h_indep_fun : iIndepFun (fun i : ℕ => fun f : ℕ → I => f i) (Measure.infinitePi fun _ => ℙ) := by
      apply_rules [ iIndepFun_iff_measure_inter_preimage_eq_mul.mpr ];
      intro S sets hsets
      generalize_proofs at *; (
      have h_prod : ∀ (S : Finset ℕ) (sets : ℕ → Set I), (∀ i ∈ S, MeasurableSet (sets i)) → (Measure.infinitePi fun _ => MeasureTheory.MeasureSpace.volume) (⋂ i ∈ S, (fun f : ℕ → I => f i) ⁻¹' sets i) = ∏ i ∈ S, (MeasureTheory.MeasureSpace.volume) (sets i) := by
        intros S sets hsets
        have h_prod : (Measure.infinitePi fun _ => MeasureTheory.MeasureSpace.volume) (⋂ i ∈ S, (fun f : ℕ → I => f i) ⁻¹' sets i) = (Measure.infinitePi fun _ => MeasureTheory.MeasureSpace.volume) (Set.pi S sets) := by
          congr with x ; aesop
        generalize_proofs at *; (
        rw [ h_prod, Measure.infinitePi_pi ] ; aesop)
      generalize_proofs at *; (
      convert h_prod S sets hsets using 1
      generalize_proofs at *; (
      refine' Finset.prod_congr rfl fun i hi => _ ; specialize h_prod { i } ( fun _ => sets i ) ; aesop;)))
    rw [ IndepFun_iff_Indep ];
    -- Apply the independence result for the infinite product measure.
    have h_indep : Indep (MeasurableSpace.comap (fun f : ℕ → I => f (n + 1)) inferInstance) (⨆ i : Iic n, MeasurableSpace.comap (fun f : ℕ → I => f i) inferInstance) (Measure.infinitePi fun _ => ℙ) := by
      have h_indep : ∀ (S T : Set ℕ), Disjoint S T → Indep (⨆ i ∈ S, MeasurableSpace.comap (fun f : ℕ → I => f i) inferInstance) (⨆ i ∈ T, MeasurableSpace.comap (fun f : ℕ → I => f i) inferInstance) (Measure.infinitePi fun _ => ℙ) := by
        apply_rules [ ProbabilityTheory.indep_iSup_of_disjoint ];
        exact fun i => measurable_pi_apply i |> Measurable.comap_le |> le_trans <| le_rfl;
      convert h_indep { n + 1 } ( Set.Iic n ) _ using 1 <;> norm_num [ Set.disjoint_left ];
      refine' le_antisymm _ _ <;> simp +decide [ iSup_le_iff, le_iSup_iff ];
    convert h_indep using 1;
    exact?;
  exact h_indep

/-
PROVIDED SOLUTION
Use indepFun_iff_map_prod_eq_prod_map_map.

We need to show:
(μ₁.prod μ₂).map (fun ω => (f₁ ω.1, (f₂ ω.1, ω.2)))
= ((μ₁.prod μ₂).map (fun ω => f₁ ω.1)).prod ((μ₁.prod μ₂).map (fun ω => (f₂ ω.1, ω.2)))

The LHS: Push (μ₁.prod μ₂) through the joint map. By Fubini / product measure properties:
= μ₁.map (fun x => (f₁ x, f₂ x)) paired with μ₂ through some reshuffling
= (μ₁.map f₁).prod (μ₁.map f₂).prod μ₂ (using h_indep via indepFun_iff_map_prod_eq_prod_map_map)

Alternatively: The RHS first marginal (μ₁.prod μ₂).map (f₁ ∘ fst) = μ₁.map f₁ (by Measure.fst_prod + map).
The second marginal (μ₁.prod μ₂).map (f₂ ∘ fst, snd) = (μ₁.map f₂).prod μ₂ (essentially).

So RHS = (μ₁.map f₁).prod ((μ₁.map f₂).prod μ₂).

The LHS can be computed as μ₁.map(f₁, f₂) reassociated with μ₂.
Using h_indep: μ₁.map(f₁, f₂) = (μ₁.map f₁).prod (μ₁.map f₂).
So LHS = ((μ₁.map f₁).prod (μ₁.map f₂)) reassociated with μ₂ = (μ₁.map f₁).prod ((μ₁.map f₂).prod μ₂) = RHS.
-/
omit [Nonempty α] [StandardBorelSpace α] [DecidableEq α] [Countable α]
  [StandardBorelSpace R] [Nonempty R] in

lemma indepFun_comp_fst_pair {Ω₁ Ω₂ β₁ β₂ : Type*}
    [mΩ₁ : MeasurableSpace Ω₁] [mΩ₂ : MeasurableSpace Ω₂]
    [mβ₁ : MeasurableSpace β₁] [mβ₂ : MeasurableSpace β₂]
    {μ₁ : Measure Ω₁} {μ₂ : Measure Ω₂}
    [IsProbabilityMeasure μ₁] [IsProbabilityMeasure μ₂]
    {f₁ : Ω₁ → β₁} {f₂ : Ω₁ → β₂}
    (hf₁ : Measurable f₁) (hf₂ : Measurable f₂)
    (h_indep : IndepFun f₁ f₂ μ₁) :
    IndepFun (fun ω : Ω₁ × Ω₂ ↦ f₁ ω.1) (fun ω ↦ (f₂ ω.1, ω.2)) (μ₁.prod μ₂) := by
  by_contra h_contra;
  obtain ⟨s₁, hs₁, s₂, hs₂, h⟩ : ∃ s₁ : Set β₁, MeasurableSet s₁ ∧ ∃ s₂ : Set (β₂ × Ω₂), MeasurableSet s₂ ∧ (μ₁.prod μ₂) {ω : Ω₁ × Ω₂ | f₁ ω.1 ∈ s₁ ∧ (f₂ ω.1, ω.2) ∈ s₂} ≠ (μ₁.prod μ₂) {ω : Ω₁ × Ω₂ | f₁ ω.1 ∈ s₁} * (μ₁.prod μ₂) {ω : Ω₁ × Ω₂ | (f₂ ω.1, ω.2) ∈ s₂} := by
    contrapose! h_contra with h_indep' ; simp_all +decide [ IndepFun ] ; (
    rw [ Kernel.indepFun_iff_measure_inter_preimage_eq_mul ] ; aesop;);
  simp_all +decide [ Set.setOf_and, MeasureTheory.Measure.prod_apply ];
  refine' h _;
  have h_prod : (μ₁.prod μ₂) ({a | f₁ a.1 ∈ s₁} ∩ {a | (f₂ a.1, a.2) ∈ s₂}) = ∫⁻ ω₂, (μ₁ {ω₁ | f₁ ω₁ ∈ s₁ ∧ (f₂ ω₁, ω₂) ∈ s₂}) ∂μ₂ := by
    rw [ MeasureTheory.Measure.prod_apply ];
    · have h_prod : ∫⁻ ω₁, μ₂ {ω₂ | f₁ ω₁ ∈ s₁ ∧ (f₂ ω₁, ω₂) ∈ s₂} ∂μ₁ = ∫⁻ ω₂, μ₁ {ω₁ | f₁ ω₁ ∈ s₁ ∧ (f₂ ω₁, ω₂) ∈ s₂} ∂μ₂ := by
        have h_measurable : MeasurableSet {p : Ω₁ × Ω₂ | f₁ p.1 ∈ s₁ ∧ (f₂ p.1, p.2) ∈ s₂} := by
          exact MeasurableSet.inter ( hf₁ hs₁ |> MeasurableSet.preimage <| measurable_fst ) ( hs₂ |> MeasurableSet.preimage <| Measurable.prodMk ( hf₂.comp measurable_fst ) measurable_snd )
        have h_prod : ∫⁻ ω₁, μ₂ {ω₂ | f₁ ω₁ ∈ s₁ ∧ (f₂ ω₁, ω₂) ∈ s₂} ∂μ₁ = ∫⁻ ω₂, μ₁ {ω₁ | f₁ ω₁ ∈ s₁ ∧ (f₂ ω₁, ω₂) ∈ s₂} ∂μ₂ := by
          have h_prod : (μ₁.prod μ₂) {p : Ω₁ × Ω₂ | f₁ p.1 ∈ s₁ ∧ (f₂ p.1, p.2) ∈ s₂} = ∫⁻ ω₁, μ₂ {ω₂ | f₁ ω₁ ∈ s₁ ∧ (f₂ ω₁, ω₂) ∈ s₂} ∂μ₁ := by
            exact?
          have h_prod' : (μ₁.prod μ₂) {p : Ω₁ × Ω₂ | f₁ p.1 ∈ s₁ ∧ (f₂ p.1, p.2) ∈ s₂} = ∫⁻ ω₂, μ₁ {ω₁ | f₁ ω₁ ∈ s₁ ∧ (f₂ ω₁, ω₂) ∈ s₂} ∂μ₂ := by
            exact?
          rw [ ← h_prod, ← h_prod' ];
        exact h_prod;
      convert h_prod using 1;
    · exact MeasurableSet.inter ( measurableSet_preimage ( hf₁.comp measurable_fst ) hs₁ ) ( measurableSet_preimage ( hf₂.comp measurable_fst |> Measurable.prodMk <| measurable_snd ) hs₂ );
  rw [ h_prod, show ( μ₁.prod μ₂ ) { a : Ω₁ × Ω₂ | f₁ a.1 ∈ s₁ } = μ₁ { ω₁ : Ω₁ | f₁ ω₁ ∈ s₁ } from ?_, show ( μ₁.prod μ₂ ) { a : Ω₁ × Ω₂ | ( f₂ a.1, a.2 ) ∈ s₂ } = ∫⁻ ω₂, μ₁ { ω₁ : Ω₁ | ( f₂ ω₁, ω₂ ) ∈ s₂ } ∂μ₂ from ?_ ];
  · rw [ ← MeasureTheory.lintegral_const_mul ];
    · refine' MeasureTheory.lintegral_congr fun ω₂ => _;
      have := h_indep.measure_inter_preimage_eq_mul;
      convert this s₁ ( { x | ( x, ω₂ ) ∈ s₂ } ) hs₁ ( measurableSet_preimage ( measurable_prodMk_right ) hs₂ ) using 1;
    · exact measurable_measure_prodMk_right ( show MeasurableSet { p : Ω₁ × Ω₂ | ( f₂ p.1, p.2 ) ∈ s₂ } from measurableSet_preimage ( hf₂.comp measurable_fst |> Measurable.prodMk <| measurable_snd ) hs₂ );
  · rw [ MeasureTheory.Measure.prod_apply ];
    · have h_fubini : ∫⁻ ω₁, μ₂ {ω₂ | (f₂ ω₁, ω₂) ∈ s₂} ∂μ₁ = ∫⁻ ω₂, μ₁ {ω₁ | (f₂ ω₁, ω₂) ∈ s₂} ∂μ₂ := by
        have h_measurable : MeasurableSet {p : Ω₁ × Ω₂ | (f₂ p.1, p.2) ∈ s₂} := by
          exact hs₂.preimage ( hf₂.comp measurable_fst |> Measurable.prodMk <| measurable_snd )
        have h_fubini : ∫⁻ ω₁, μ₂ {ω₂ | (f₂ ω₁, ω₂) ∈ s₂} ∂μ₁ = ∫⁻ ω₂, μ₁ {ω₁ | (f₂ ω₁, ω₂) ∈ s₂} ∂μ₂ := by
          have h_prod : (μ₁.prod μ₂) {p : Ω₁ × Ω₂ | (f₂ p.1, p.2) ∈ s₂} = ∫⁻ ω₁, μ₂ {ω₂ | (f₂ ω₁, ω₂) ∈ s₂} ∂μ₁ := by
            exact?
          have h_prod' : (μ₁.prod μ₂) {p : Ω₁ × Ω₂ | (f₂ p.1, p.2) ∈ s₂} = ∫⁻ ω₂, μ₁ {ω₁ | (f₂ ω₁, ω₂) ∈ s₂} ∂μ₂ := by
            exact?
          rw [h_prod, h_prod'] at *;
        exact h_fubini;
      exact h_fubini;
    · exact measurableSet_preimage ( hf₂.comp measurable_fst |> Measurable.prodMk <| measurable_snd ) hs₂;
  · erw [ show { a : Ω₁ × Ω₂ | f₁ a.1 ∈ s₁ } = ( { ω₁ : Ω₁ | f₁ ω₁ ∈ s₁ } ×ˢ Set.univ ) by ext ; aesop, MeasureTheory.Measure.prod_prod ] ; simp +decide [ hs₁ ]

/-
PROBLEM
ω.1 (n+1) is independent from the pair ((fun i : Iic n ↦ ω.1 i), ω.2).

PROVIDED SOLUTION
Direct application of indepFun_comp_fst_pair with f₁ = eval(n+1) and f₂ = restrict(Iic n), using indepFun_eval_restrict_infinitePi as the independence hypothesis.
-/
lemma indepFun_fst_add_one_of_pair (ν : Kernel α R) [IsMarkovKernel ν] (n : ℕ) :
    IndepFun (fun (ω : probSpace α R) ↦ ω.1 (n + 1))
      (fun ω ↦ (fun (i : Iic n) ↦ ω.1 i, ω.2)) (arrayMeasure ν) := by
  have h_indep := indepFun_eval_restrict_infinitePi n
  exact indepFun_comp_fst_pair (by fun_prop)
    (measurable_pi_lambda _ fun _ => measurable_pi_apply _) h_indep

/-
PROVIDED SOLUTION
Obtain f, hf_meas, hf_eq from hist_factors_through_pair alg n.
Then hist alg ω n = f (fun i ↦ ω.1 i, ω.2), so hist alg · n = f ∘ (fun ω ↦ (fun i ↦ ω.1 i, ω.2)).
Apply (indepFun_fst_add_one_of_pair ν n).comp measurable_id hf_meas, then convert using the functional equality.
-/
lemma indepFun_fst_add_one_hist (alg : Algorithm α R) (ν : Kernel α R) [IsMarkovKernel ν] (n : ℕ) :
    IndepFun (fun ω ↦ ω.1 (n + 1)) (hist alg · n) (arrayMeasure ν) := by
  convert ( indepFun_fst_add_one_of_pair ν n ).comp measurable_id _ using 1;
  convert rfl;
  rotate_left;
  exact fun p => hist_factors_through_pair alg n |> Classical.choose |> fun f => f p;
  · exact Classical.choose_spec ( hist_factors_through_pair alg n ) |>.1;
  · exact Classical.choose_spec ( hist_factors_through_pair alg n ) |>.2 _ ▸ rfl

lemma hasCondDistrib_action' (alg : Algorithm α R) (ν : Kernel α R) [IsMarkovKernel ν] (n : ℕ) :
    HasCondDistrib (action alg (n + 1)) (hist alg · n) (alg.policy n) (arrayMeasure ν) := by
  rw [action_add_one_eq]
  have h_fun ω := algFunction_map alg n (hist alg ω n)
  refine ⟨by fun_prop, by fun_prop, ?_⟩
  refine condDistrib_ae_eq_of_measure_eq_compProd _ (by fun_prop) ?_
  have h_indep : (arrayMeasure ν).map (fun ω ↦ (ω.1 (n + 1), hist alg ω n)) =
      (ℙ).prod ((arrayMeasure ν).map (hist alg · n)) := by
    have h_indep' := indepFun_fst_add_one_hist alg ν n
    rw [indepFun_iff_map_prod_eq_prod_map_map (by fun_prop) (by fun_prop)] at h_indep'
    rw [h_indep']
    congr
    simp only [arrayMeasure]
    calc ((Measure.infinitePi fun x ↦ ℙ).prod (Bandit.streamMeasure ν)).map (fun ω ↦ ω.1 (n + 1))
    _ = (Measure.infinitePi fun x ↦ ℙ).map (Function.eval (n + 1)) := by
      nth_rw 2 [← Measure.fst_prod (μ := Measure.infinitePi fun x ↦ ℙ)
        (ν := Bandit.streamMeasure ν)]
      rw [Measure.fst, Measure.map_map (by fun_prop) (by fun_prop)]
      rfl
    _ = ℙ := by rw [Measure.infinitePi_map_eval]
  have : (fun x ↦ (hist alg x n, algFunction alg n (hist alg x n) (x.1 (n + 1)))) =
      (fun p ↦ (p.2, algFunction alg n (p.2) (p.1))) ∘ (fun x ↦ (x.1 (n + 1), hist alg x n)) := rfl
  rw [this, ← Measure.map_map (by fun_prop) (by fun_prop), h_indep]
  have : (ℙ : Measure I).prod ((arrayMeasure ν).map (hist alg · n)) =
      ((Kernel.const _ ℙ) ×ₖ Kernel.id) ∘ₘ ((arrayMeasure ν).map (hist alg · n)) := by
    have h := Measure.compProd_const (μ := (arrayMeasure ν).map (hist alg · n))
      (ν := (ℙ : Measure I))
    rw [Measure.compProd_eq_comp_prod] at h
    rw [← Measure.prod_swap, ← h, ← Measure.deterministic_comp_eq_map (by fun_prop),
      Measure.comp_assoc, ← Kernel.swap, Kernel.swap_prod]
  rw [this, ← Measure.deterministic_comp_eq_map (by fun_prop),
    ← Measure.deterministic_comp_eq_map (by fun_prop), Measure.compProd_eq_comp_prod,
    Measure.comp_assoc, Measure.comp_assoc, Measure.comp_assoc]
  congr 2
  ext ω : 1
  simp only [Kernel.deterministic_comp_eq_map, Kernel.comp_deterministic_eq_comap, Kernel.coe_comap,
    Function.comp_apply]
  rw [Kernel.map_apply _ (by fun_prop), Kernel.prod_apply, Kernel.const_apply, Kernel.id_apply,
    Kernel.prod_apply, Kernel.id_apply, ← h_fun]
  calc (((ℙ).prod (Measure.dirac (hist alg ω n)))).map (fun p ↦ (p.2, algFunction alg n p.2 p.1))
  _ = (((ℙ).prod (Measure.dirac (hist alg ω n))).map Prod.swap).map
      (fun p ↦ (p.1, algFunction alg n p.1 p.2)) := by
    rw [Measure.map_map (by fun_prop) (by fun_prop)]
    rfl
  _ = ((Measure.dirac (hist alg ω n)).prod ℙ).map (fun p ↦ (p.1, algFunction alg n p.1 p.2)) := by
    rw [Measure.prod_swap]
  _ = (Measure.dirac (hist alg ω n)).prod ((ℙ).map (algFunction alg n (hist alg ω n))) := by
    ext s hs
    rw [Measure.map_apply (by fun_prop) hs, Measure.prod_apply, lintegral_dirac, Measure.prod_apply,
      lintegral_dirac, Measure.map_apply (by fun_prop)]
    · congr
    · exact hs.preimage (by fun_prop)
    · exact hs
    · exact hs.preimage (by fun_prop)

lemma hasCondDistrib_reward' (alg : Algorithm α R) (ν : Kernel α R) [IsMarkovKernel ν]
    (n : ℕ) :
    HasCondDistrib (reward alg (n + 1)) (fun ω ↦ (hist alg ω n, action alg (n + 1) ω))
      (ν.prodMkLeft _) (arrayMeasure ν) := by
  rw [reward_eq]
  refine ⟨?_, by fun_prop, ?_⟩
  · sorry
  refine condDistrib_ae_eq_of_measure_eq_compProd _ ?_ ?_
  · sorry
  sorry

lemma hasCondDistrib_action (alg : Algorithm α R) (ν : Kernel α R) [IsMarkovKernel ν] (n : ℕ) :
    HasCondDistrib (action alg (n + 1))
      (fun ω (i : Iic n) ↦ (action alg i ω, reward alg i ω))
      (alg.policy n) (arrayMeasure ν) := by
  convert hasCondDistrib_action' alg ν n with ω i
  · simp only [action]
    rw [hist_eq _ _ n]
  · simp only [reward]
    rw [hist_eq _ _ n]

lemma hasCondDistrib_reward (alg : Algorithm α R) (ν : Kernel α R) [IsMarkovKernel ν]
    (n : ℕ) :
    HasCondDistrib (reward alg (n + 1))
      (fun ω ↦ (fun (i : Iic n) ↦ (action alg i ω, reward alg i ω), action alg (n + 1) ω))
      ((stationaryEnv ν).feedback n) (arrayMeasure ν) := by
  convert hasCondDistrib_reward' alg ν n with ω i
  · simp only [action]
    rw [hist_eq _ _ n]
  · simp only [reward]
    rw [hist_eq _ _ n]

lemma isAlgEnvSeq_arrayMeasure (alg : Algorithm α R) (ν : Kernel α R) [IsMarkovKernel ν] :
    IsAlgEnvSeq (action alg) (reward alg) alg (stationaryEnv ν) (arrayMeasure ν) where
  hasLaw_action_zero := hasLaw_action_zero alg ν
  hasCondDistrib_reward_zero := hasCondDistrib_reward_zero alg ν
  hasCondDistrib_action := hasCondDistrib_action alg ν
  hasCondDistrib_reward := hasCondDistrib_reward alg ν

end ArrayModel

